1
00:00:15,500 --> 00:00:17,500
If you don't want to kill Tian,

2
00:00:18,000 --> 00:00:21,500
you have to find out what his secret is.

3
00:00:21,700 --> 00:00:24,500
Someone wants to apply for a job.

4
00:00:25,500 --> 00:00:27,500
If I was in trouble, I should come to you.

5
00:00:28,000 --> 00:00:29,500
So what would you like to work on?

6
00:00:29,700 --> 00:00:31,500
I'm illiterate. I can't read and write.

7
00:00:31,800 --> 00:00:32,500
I can only do the labor job.

8
00:00:33,000 --> 00:00:33,500
but you learn.

9
00:00:34,500 --> 00:00:35,500
I'll be the one to teach you.

10
00:00:36,000 --> 00:00:36,500
Even if you start a little late,

11
00:00:37,500 --> 00:00:38,500
but I believe you can do it anyway.

12
00:00:41,500 --> 00:00:44,500
I had it checked by Doctor Qi to know that the owner of this tooth

13
00:00:44,700 --> 00:00:45,500
died because of the beetle orchids.

14
00:00:46,200 --> 00:00:48,500
You two used the beetle orchids to kill someone

15
00:00:48,900 --> 00:00:50,500
to hide Tian's secret, right?

16
00:00:50,700 --> 00:00:51,500
I didn't do anything wrong.

17
00:00:51,800 --> 00:00:52,500
You still don't accept it?

18
00:00:53,500 --> 00:00:55,500
Go to Jia's room. Search for the beetle orchid.

19
00:00:56,200 --> 00:00:56,500
There's nothing, Sir.

20
00:00:57,300 --> 00:00:57,500
I have one.

21
00:00:58,300 --> 00:00:59,500
Tell them what you saw.

22
00:00:59,800 --> 00:01:03,500
I saw Aunt Jia buried those orchids in the forest at the back of the house.

23
00:01:04,000 --> 00:01:05,500
Go to the forest at the back of our house now.

24
00:01:05,700 --> 00:01:08,500
Your madam killed Dong to hide a secret for Tian.

25
00:01:09,500 --> 00:01:12,500
Today is the day that I will get the evidence to arrest her.

26
00:03:10,500 --> 00:03:11,500
Sir.

27
00:03:17,500 --> 00:03:18,500
Chan.

28
00:03:19,500 --> 00:03:21,500
Why did you call everyone?

29
00:03:23,500 --> 00:03:27,500
I didn't. I just walked by and everyone follow me.

30
00:03:28,500 --> 00:03:29,500
But that's good.

31
00:03:29,800 --> 00:03:32,500
Everyone here will be able to see the evidence at the same time.

32
00:03:32,800 --> 00:03:36,500
What did Madam and Jia use to kill Dong?

33
00:03:37,500 --> 00:03:38,500
Chan.

34
00:03:50,500 --> 00:03:52,500
You are here now, the origin of this story.

35
00:03:53,500 --> 00:03:57,500
Let's see what your mother did

36
00:03:58,500 --> 00:04:01,500
because she wanted to hide your secret.

37
00:04:02,500 --> 00:04:05,500
Madam Li even used these peculiar herbs to kill someone.

38
00:04:16,500 --> 00:04:17,500
Madam.

39
00:04:19,500 --> 00:04:20,500
If I am not here anymore,

40
00:04:22,500 --> 00:04:26,500
you and Mr. Tian have to take good care of yourself.

41
00:04:27,500 --> 00:04:28,500
What are you going to do?

42
00:04:29,500 --> 00:04:31,500
I will take all responsibility myself.

43
00:04:33,500 --> 00:04:35,500
I'll ensure that it won't get to you.

44
00:04:39,500 --> 00:04:41,500
Please hold a funeral for me.

45
00:04:46,500 --> 00:04:47,500
Jia.

46
00:04:59,500 --> 00:05:00,500
We’ve found the box, Sir.

47
00:05:21,500 --> 00:05:25,500
This box is the one Jia buried.

48
00:05:42,500 --> 00:05:43,500
Bao. / Yes, Sir.

49
00:05:44,500 --> 00:05:45,500
Unwrap the box.

50
00:06:32,500 --> 00:06:33,500
This is an empty box.

51
00:06:39,500 --> 00:06:40,500
What does it mean?

52
00:06:45,500 --> 00:06:46,500
Empty?

53
00:06:48,500 --> 00:06:49,500
Do you point out the wrong site?

54
00:06:50,500 --> 00:06:51,500
How is that possible?

55
00:06:52,500 --> 00:06:56,500
I saw with my own eyes that Jia put the orchid into the box and buried it here.

56
00:06:59,500 --> 00:07:01,500
I told you that there was nothing.

57
00:07:02,500 --> 00:07:04,500
Jia and I didn't hide anything.

58
00:07:05,300 --> 00:07:07,500
Who buried this box?

59
00:07:12,500 --> 00:07:16,500
It would probably be the one who slandered us, Sir.

60
00:07:17,500 --> 00:07:19,500
That's strange. Slandering

61
00:07:20,500 --> 00:07:22,500
by burying an empty box here?

62
00:07:23,500 --> 00:07:26,500
Do you believe in someone who has slandered me?

63
00:07:27,500 --> 00:07:30,500
I told you that I didn't hurt anyone.

64
00:07:54,500 --> 00:07:55,500
Since there is no evidence,

65
00:07:56,500 --> 00:07:58,500
I will continue to investigate this case

66
00:07:59,500 --> 00:08:00,500
until the truth is found.

67
00:08:04,500 --> 00:08:05,500
Doctor.

68
00:08:07,500 --> 00:08:10,500
You must stay here with me, helping me find the truth.

69
00:08:11,500 --> 00:08:12,500
Yes, Sir.

70
00:08:35,500 --> 00:08:37,500
Nuan really saw it.

71
00:08:38,100 --> 00:08:38,500
But I don't know why it's an empty box.

72
00:08:39,500 --> 00:08:40,500
Nuan, are you mistaken?

73
00:08:41,500 --> 00:08:43,500
No, I am not. I really saw that.

74
00:08:44,000 --> 00:08:45,500
I saw Jia took the orchids out

75
00:08:46,100 --> 00:08:47,500
before putting it in the box.

76
00:08:48,500 --> 00:08:51,500
Sir, even though Nuan is a bit dumb,

77
00:08:52,000 --> 00:08:53,500
but she's not a liar.

78
00:08:57,500 --> 00:08:58,500
Chan, Nuan.

79
00:08:59,500 --> 00:09:01,500
From now on, you two don't interfere with this anymore.

80
00:09:02,500 --> 00:09:05,500
Why? I'm not lying, Sir.

81
00:09:05,800 --> 00:09:06,500
Nuan really saw it.

82
00:09:07,000 --> 00:09:09,500
Chan, everyone knows

83
00:09:10,500 --> 00:09:11,500
that you and Li don't get along.

84
00:09:12,500 --> 00:09:13,500
You always tried to beat her.

85
00:09:14,500 --> 00:09:16,500
People will think that you try to create false evidence.

86
00:09:17,500 --> 00:09:18,500
to slander her.

87
00:09:19,500 --> 00:09:21,500
Or lending someone else's hand to attack her.

88
00:09:22,500 --> 00:09:23,500
So you don't interfere with this again.

89
00:09:26,500 --> 00:09:28,500
From now on, let me handle this on my own.

90
00:09:30,500 --> 00:09:31,500
Fine.

91
00:09:32,500 --> 00:09:35,500
But I hope that if you know the truth,

92
00:09:36,500 --> 00:09:38,500
you will judge this matter fairly.

93
00:09:49,500 --> 00:09:51,500
Where is the orchid in the box? Who took it?

94
00:09:52,500 --> 00:09:53,500
Right, Madam.

95
00:09:54,000 --> 00:09:56,500
It means that someone else has saw it that time besides Nuan.

96
00:09:57,200 --> 00:10:01,500
This time we might be lucky that a thief stole it before Mr. Song caught us.

97
00:10:02,500 --> 00:10:05,500
But the disappearance is definitely not good for us.

98
00:10:06,500 --> 00:10:08,500
Who took the orchids?

99
00:11:36,500 --> 00:11:37,500
You still haven't slept yet?

100
00:11:44,500 --> 00:11:45,500
You're worried about what happened today?

101
00:12:09,500 --> 00:12:10,500
Don't think too much.

102
00:12:11,500 --> 00:12:13,500
How can I not think too much?

103
00:12:15,500 --> 00:12:16,500
You saw it too.

104
00:12:19,500 --> 00:12:20,500
What happened today?

105
00:12:24,500 --> 00:12:25,500
I...

106
00:12:29,500 --> 00:12:31,500
I'm so stressed that I don't know what to do.

107
00:12:34,500 --> 00:12:35,500
Then you can tell me.

108
00:12:38,500 --> 00:12:42,500
We are friends, I can listen to you.

109
00:12:52,500 --> 00:12:53,500
I...

110
00:13:00,500 --> 00:13:01,500
I'm not like everyone else.

111
00:13:04,500 --> 00:13:07,500
I am the cause of all problems.

112
00:13:08,500 --> 00:13:09,500
If I wasn't here,

113
00:13:11,500 --> 00:13:13,500
everyone would be happier.

114
00:13:15,500 --> 00:13:17,500
I made my parents miserable.

115
00:13:19,500 --> 00:13:20,500
Made everyone suffer.

116
00:13:23,500 --> 00:13:25,500
Sometimes, I thought that...

117
00:13:28,500 --> 00:13:29,500
If I died,

118
00:13:31,500 --> 00:13:33,500
everyone would be happier.

119
00:13:59,500 --> 00:14:00,500
Don't say that.

120
00:14:02,500 --> 00:14:04,500
Your life is precious.

121
00:14:06,500 --> 00:14:10,500
Do you know what the servants here say about you?

122
00:14:14,500 --> 00:14:17,500
They say you're humble,

123
00:14:19,500 --> 00:14:23,500
kind, and don't take advantage of the inferior.

124
00:14:26,500 --> 00:14:27,500
They love you.

125
00:14:30,500 --> 00:14:31,500
Me too.

126
00:14:42,500 --> 00:14:43,500
I...

127
00:14:44,500 --> 00:14:45,500
I mean Fu and Mei.

128
00:14:46,500 --> 00:14:48,500
They think you're kind, so they love you.

129
00:14:58,500 --> 00:14:59,500
I...

130
00:15:02,500 --> 00:15:03,500
Thanks a lot.

131
00:15:07,500 --> 00:15:12,500
Talking to you makes me feel much better.

132
00:15:25,500 --> 00:15:26,500
Stay still.

133
00:15:42,500 --> 00:15:43,500
Tian.

134
00:15:44,500 --> 00:15:45,500
Mother.

135
00:15:48,500 --> 00:15:50,500
What are you doing here at late night?

136
00:15:52,500 --> 00:15:53,500
I...

137
00:15:54,500 --> 00:15:55,500
I...

138
00:16:14,500 --> 00:16:17,000
How dare you do this, huh?

139
00:16:17,000 --> 00:16:19,500
Bringing a man to flirt with each other in our house. Who is he?

140
00:16:19,500 --> 00:16:22,500
Mother, he is my friend.

141
00:16:22,500 --> 00:16:24,500
I brought him to work with me.

142
00:16:24,500 --> 00:16:26,000
Are you sure that's all?

143
00:16:26,000 --> 00:16:30,000
Do you dare enough to bring a man closer to you here?

144
00:16:30,000 --> 00:16:32,000
What crime did I do?

145
00:16:32,000 --> 00:16:34,500
I want a daughter-in-law, but what I get is a son-in-law instead.

146
00:16:34,500 --> 00:16:37,500
Mother, it's nothing.

147
00:16:38,000 --> 00:16:40,500
I'm just worried and he came to talk to me.

148
00:16:40,500 --> 00:16:44,500
Your life is much better than others. Why are you so worried?

149
00:16:44,500 --> 00:16:46,500
Is there anything to worry about, you say?

150
00:17:11,000 --> 00:17:12,500
So it's you who took it?

151
00:17:12,500 --> 00:17:14,500
Yes, it's me.

152
00:17:17,500 --> 00:17:19,500
I saw Auntie Jia hiding the orchid.

153
00:17:20,500 --> 00:17:22,500
I'm afraid that she will use it to hurt someone else later.

154
00:17:23,500 --> 00:17:25,500
So I took it and kept it myself.

155
00:17:28,500 --> 00:17:30,500
The evidence is so obvious,

156
00:17:31,500 --> 00:17:33,500
are you going to accept now that you have killed someone?

157
00:17:34,500 --> 00:17:37,500
You killed to hide that I am a homosexual.

158
00:17:38,500 --> 00:17:39,500
If I really did it,

159
00:17:40,500 --> 00:17:41,500
so what are you going to do?

160
00:17:43,500 --> 00:17:44,500
Mother.

161
00:17:46,500 --> 00:17:47,500
Why are you doing this?

162
00:17:48,500 --> 00:17:51,500
Why are you doing this? I've never wanted this, Mother.

163
00:17:51,700 --> 00:17:52,500
Don't you know?

164
00:17:53,500 --> 00:17:56,500
Don't you know why I did this?

165
00:18:04,500 --> 00:18:07,500
You want to maintain your power. You want to be the madam.

166
00:18:08,000 --> 00:18:10,500
You want me to be fascinated by power like you.

167
00:18:11,500 --> 00:18:15,500
If everyone knows what I am, you will lose everything.

168
00:18:19,500 --> 00:18:22,500
Can't you see the love that I have for you?

169
00:18:26,500 --> 00:18:30,500
If I am such a bad woman... If I was an evil,

170
00:18:31,500 --> 00:18:34,500
go tell your father to bring the police to arrest me.

171
00:18:38,500 --> 00:18:39,500
Mother.

172
00:19:48,500 --> 00:19:49,500
So you and Aunt Jia

173
00:19:50,500 --> 00:19:52,500
won't be able to use them to kill anyone again.

174
00:20:27,500 --> 00:20:29,500
Tian, are you sleeping?

175
00:20:30,500 --> 00:20:31,500
May I come in?

176
00:20:34,500 --> 00:20:35,500
Yes.

177
00:20:46,500 --> 00:20:48,500
What's the matter? You come here so late.

178
00:20:59,500 --> 00:21:00,500
I want to apologize

179
00:21:01,500 --> 00:21:04,500
that my mother and Nuan caused chaos,

180
00:21:05,000 --> 00:21:06,500
make you and Madam Li to be in trouble again.

181
00:21:11,500 --> 00:21:14,500
You don't have to apologize or feel guilty about anything, Yang.

182
00:21:17,500 --> 00:21:18,500
In fact,

183
00:21:20,500 --> 00:21:24,500
You or Aunt Chan didn't make all of these things to happen.

184
00:21:30,500 --> 00:21:33,500
It's me who is the cause of everything.

185
00:21:35,500 --> 00:21:36,500
You know that too.

186
00:21:41,500 --> 00:21:42,500
Tian.

187
00:21:43,500 --> 00:21:45,500
You told me to stop blaming myself.

188
00:21:46,500 --> 00:21:49,500
But it's you who should stop thinking like this.

189
00:21:50,500 --> 00:21:55,500
It's not that you can choose or want all the things to happen.

190
00:21:57,500 --> 00:21:59,500
Thank you very much, Yang.

191
00:22:01,500 --> 00:22:02,500
About Aunt Chan,

192
00:22:03,500 --> 00:22:06,500
don't think too much. I'm not angry at all.

193
00:22:08,500 --> 00:22:09,500
Tian.

194
00:22:13,500 --> 00:22:14,500
You can get angry.

195
00:22:15,500 --> 00:22:18,500
I know my mom keeps causing troubles.

196
00:22:19,100 --> 00:22:21,500
And I don't know if she's going to make up a story again.

197
00:22:23,500 --> 00:22:26,500
But if she makes up something without any evidence like before,

198
00:22:27,500 --> 00:22:29,500
I guess no one will believe it.

199
00:22:30,100 --> 00:22:33,500
I think you have a negative attitude towards your mom.

200
00:22:34,500 --> 00:22:37,500
If Aunt Chan was not confident, she wouldn't probably say it.

201
00:22:38,500 --> 00:22:39,500
What do you mean?

202
00:22:40,500 --> 00:22:42,500
You said as if you knew something.

203
00:22:44,500 --> 00:22:45,500
It's nothing.

204
00:22:47,500 --> 00:22:50,500
So from now on,

205
00:22:52,500 --> 00:22:55,500
no one here will be harmed again.

206
00:22:56,500 --> 00:22:57,500
Don't worry anymore.

207
00:23:30,500 --> 00:23:33,500
Where are Li and Chan?

208
00:23:34,500 --> 00:23:36,500
I've arrived here long ago, but I didn't see them.

209
00:23:40,500 --> 00:23:42,500
Do you have any business with those two?

210
00:23:43,500 --> 00:23:45,500
I just wanted to say hello.

211
00:23:45,800 --> 00:23:48,500
I haven't visited you for a long time.

212
00:23:49,500 --> 00:23:54,500
Honestly, you look haggard.

213
00:23:57,500 --> 00:24:00,500
It's not like you're working hard, since you got Tian to help you.

214
00:24:01,500 --> 00:24:05,500
Or do you worry at something?

215
00:24:06,500 --> 00:24:08,500
You can tell me.

216
00:24:26,500 --> 00:24:27,500
It is.

217
00:24:31,500 --> 00:24:32,500
Something strange happened.

218
00:24:34,500 --> 00:24:35,500
Something strange?

219
00:24:38,500 --> 00:24:40,500
What's the matter, big brother?

220
00:24:45,500 --> 00:24:46,500
The strange thing is...

221
00:24:50,500 --> 00:24:51,500
That you come to see me today.

222
00:24:55,500 --> 00:24:56,500
Don't claim that it is the accounting.

223
00:24:58,500 --> 00:25:00,500
Because it's not the billing cycle yet.

224
00:25:04,500 --> 00:25:06,500
Yesterday, something happened in my house.

225
00:25:08,500 --> 00:25:09,500
When it’s morning, you come here.

226
00:25:10,500 --> 00:25:16,500
Not to mention when you and Ma brought the police to attack my family member.

227
00:25:19,500 --> 00:25:20,500
I haven't investigate the cause yet.

228
00:25:23,500 --> 00:25:26,500
Then you brought me someone who claimed to be Dong's relative.

229
00:25:27,500 --> 00:25:30,500
You know every movement of my family very well.

230
00:25:32,500 --> 00:25:33,500
Or did someone...

231
00:25:36,500 --> 00:25:38,500
tell you about this?

232
00:25:47,500 --> 00:25:49,500
Do you think too much?

233
00:25:52,500 --> 00:25:54,500
Every incident,

234
00:25:55,500 --> 00:25:57,500
it's because I really care about you.

235
00:26:00,500 --> 00:26:01,500
Someone like me

236
00:26:02,500 --> 00:26:05,500
will never harm you.

237
00:26:07,500 --> 00:26:08,500
Sometimes,

238
00:26:12,500 --> 00:26:13,500
we don't know someone deep down.

239
00:26:15,500 --> 00:26:17,500
You must be tired today.

240
00:26:18,500 --> 00:26:22,500
I think I'd better leave now.

241
00:26:24,500 --> 00:26:25,500
Goodbye, big brother.

242
00:26:52,500 --> 00:26:53,500
This way, Madam.

243
00:26:57,500 --> 00:26:59,500
We were almost caught.

244
00:26:59,800 --> 00:27:01,500
I did a mistake myself.

245
00:27:01,500 --> 00:27:02,500
I want to know about the incident so I hurry here.

246
00:27:03,500 --> 00:27:06,500
I didn't think that it would make Big Brother suspicious.

247
00:27:08,500 --> 00:27:11,500
You too. When you want to send me news from now on,

248
00:27:11,800 --> 00:27:13,500
be more careful.

249
00:27:14,000 --> 00:27:14,500
Yes, Madam.

250
00:27:20,500 --> 00:27:22,500
Who is with Tian?

251
00:27:23,500 --> 00:27:26,500
It's Jiu, a new worker here.

252
00:27:26,800 --> 00:27:27,500
He looks good.

253
00:27:29,500 --> 00:27:30,500
Worker?

254
00:27:32,500 --> 00:27:33,500
But why do they seems so close?

255
00:27:34,500 --> 00:27:36,500
It's like they've known each other before.

256
00:27:41,500 --> 00:27:42,500
Tian.

257
00:27:45,500 --> 00:27:46,500
Be careful.

258
00:27:47,500 --> 00:27:49,500
I'm clumsy.

259
00:27:50,500 --> 00:27:53,500
He's handsome and strong.

260
00:27:54,500 --> 00:27:56,500
Don't fall in love with a man now.

261
00:27:57,500 --> 00:27:58,500
Can't you see that there is something strange?

262
00:28:03,500 --> 00:28:05,500
What strange?

263
00:28:10,500 --> 00:28:12,500
I can't explain either.

264
00:28:16,500 --> 00:28:20,500
Let's just keep an eye on these two as well.

265
00:28:21,500 --> 00:28:23,500
And don't be so obsessed with this worker.

266
00:28:24,100 --> 00:28:28,500
Don't forget that your main job is to become a wife of Tian as soon as possible.

267
00:28:29,500 --> 00:28:33,500
The day when he becomes the head of the Five Dragons Association,

268
00:28:34,500 --> 00:28:37,500
he can help support our teahouse business.

269
00:28:38,500 --> 00:28:39,500
Yes, Madam.

270
00:28:53,500 --> 00:28:54,500
Your herbal soup, sir.

271
00:29:11,500 --> 00:29:14,500
Sir, your medicine.

272
00:29:16,500 --> 00:29:17,500
Madam.

273
00:29:44,500 --> 00:29:46,500
Thank you, Doctor. / Yes.

274
00:29:58,500 --> 00:30:00,500
What does this mean?

275
00:30:01,500 --> 00:30:05,500
From now on, Doctor Qi will be the one who prescribes medicine for me.

276
00:30:07,500 --> 00:30:08,500
Why?

277
00:30:09,500 --> 00:30:11,500
Jia is already doing this duty.

278
00:30:13,500 --> 00:30:16,500
Or you don't trust me, thinking I will poison you?

279
00:30:18,500 --> 00:30:22,500
If it was in the past, I would never have thought of it that way.

280
00:30:23,200 --> 00:30:24,500
But a lot of things happened.

281
00:30:25,500 --> 00:30:27,500
I can't trust anyone.

282
00:30:28,500 --> 00:30:30,500
Including me, right?

283
00:30:32,500 --> 00:30:34,500
I have been your wife for over twenty years.

284
00:30:35,500 --> 00:30:40,500
The good things I have done all the time didn't mean anything, right?

285
00:30:41,100 --> 00:30:41,500
Of course it did.

286
00:30:42,500 --> 00:30:43,500
Why didn't it mean anything?

287
00:30:45,500 --> 00:30:47,500
In the past, I have always loved and thought that

288
00:30:48,500 --> 00:30:52,500
you are the one who deserves to be my wife,

289
00:30:53,500 --> 00:30:55,500
and the mother of the Song Family.

290
00:30:56,500 --> 00:30:58,500
You never disgraced me.

291
00:30:59,500 --> 00:31:01,500
You never brought me a hard time.

292
00:31:03,500 --> 00:31:04,500
You never disappointed me.

293
00:31:07,500 --> 00:31:09,500
But today you are not.

294
00:31:13,500 --> 00:31:14,500
You aren't the old Li that I knew.

295
00:31:18,500 --> 00:31:20,500
I have no way of knowing your heart,

296
00:31:21,500 --> 00:31:23,500
of what you're able to do today.

297
00:31:24,500 --> 00:31:28,500
If you don't trust me anymore, just send me to the authorities

298
00:31:29,500 --> 00:31:30,500
or kill me now.

299
00:31:31,500 --> 00:31:35,500
It's still better than being a villain in your eyes. It feels like I’m already dead anyway.

300
00:31:36,300 --> 00:31:37,500
Do you think I am happy?

301
00:31:38,500 --> 00:31:40,500
Do you think I am not in pain?

302
00:31:52,500 --> 00:31:53,500
Li.

303
00:31:54,500 --> 00:31:56,500
If you want me to trust you,

304
00:31:58,500 --> 00:31:59,500
why don't you trust me?

305
00:32:00,500 --> 00:32:02,500
What's going on?

306
00:32:03,000 --> 00:32:03,500
Why didn't you tell me?

307
00:32:04,500 --> 00:32:05,500
What happened?

308
00:32:07,500 --> 00:32:09,500
What is Tian's secret? Tell me.

309
00:32:12,500 --> 00:32:13,500
Li.

310
00:32:15,500 --> 00:32:17,500
I'm also Tian's father.

311
00:32:19,500 --> 00:32:24,500
You think that if I knew it, I would be able to hurt and destroy my son?

312
00:32:27,500 --> 00:32:28,500
Tell me.

313
00:32:29,500 --> 00:32:31,500
What's going on?

314
00:32:33,500 --> 00:32:34,500
Well...

315
00:32:40,500 --> 00:32:43,500
There's no secret.

316
00:32:53,500 --> 00:32:54,500
Fine, fine.

317
00:32:58,500 --> 00:33:00,500
You want it to be this way?

318
00:33:01,500 --> 00:33:03,500
Since you don't accept it,

319
00:33:04,500 --> 00:33:07,500
If the truth is revealed one day,

320
00:33:12,500 --> 00:33:14,500
don't say that I'm evil.

321
00:33:47,500 --> 00:33:48,500
I'd like to talk to you.

322
00:34:00,500 --> 00:34:02,500
I thought that I would never see you again.

323
00:34:03,500 --> 00:34:07,500
Because since the incident happened, you always avoid me.

324
00:34:08,500 --> 00:34:11,500
Actually, when I come to stay here,

325
00:34:12,500 --> 00:34:15,500
the happiest person should be you.

326
00:34:16,500 --> 00:34:19,500
That's right. I should be glad.

327
00:34:20,500 --> 00:34:22,500
But I am disappointed that you came back.

328
00:34:24,500 --> 00:34:27,500
You are sad because you're afraid that if I am here,

329
00:34:28,500 --> 00:34:30,500
you and Madam will do something with difficulty.

330
00:34:31,500 --> 00:34:35,500
Or are you thinking of using the beetle orchid to kill someone again?

331
00:34:38,500 --> 00:34:39,500
Jia.

332
00:34:40,500 --> 00:34:44,500
Do you realize that what you did was a bad thing?

333
00:34:45,500 --> 00:34:46,500
You are like a doctor.

334
00:34:47,500 --> 00:34:51,500
I taught you knowledge and skills to save people's lives.

335
00:34:52,000 --> 00:34:53,500
But why did you use it to kill someone like this?

336
00:34:54,500 --> 00:34:59,500
If you still have a conscience, admit what happened to Mr. Song.

337
00:35:00,300 --> 00:35:01,500
And don't do such terrible things again.

338
00:35:03,500 --> 00:35:04,500
I can't admit it

339
00:35:05,500 --> 00:35:06,500
because I didn't do it.

340
00:35:06,700 --> 00:35:08,500
We've come to this point and you still won't admit it?

341
00:35:09,500 --> 00:35:13,500
Let Madam Li manage these household affairs.

342
00:35:15,500 --> 00:35:16,500
She is a good person.

343
00:35:17,500 --> 00:35:19,500
I am indebted to her.

344
00:35:21,500 --> 00:35:24,500
If you pretend that nothings happened and don't get in our way, will it be possible?

345
00:35:28,500 --> 00:35:29,500
Doctor.

346
00:35:31,500 --> 00:35:32,500
if you are here,

347
00:35:33,500 --> 00:35:35,500
it doesn't benefit to anyone.

348
00:35:37,500 --> 00:35:42,500
You should leave this place to give treatment to others who needs help from you.

349
00:35:43,500 --> 00:35:44,500
No.

350
00:35:45,500 --> 00:35:49,500
I must stay until the truth becomes clear.

351
00:35:50,500 --> 00:35:53,500
Because if I leave, someone else might die

352
00:35:54,500 --> 00:35:56,500
or is harmed by the knowledge that I taught you.

353
00:35:58,500 --> 00:36:00,500
I won't let that happen.

354
00:36:30,500 --> 00:36:34,500
Mr. Tian may like this smell of incense cone.

355
00:36:35,000 --> 00:36:35,500
He can relax.

356
00:36:36,500 --> 00:36:38,500
Anything could be easier.

357
00:36:51,500 --> 00:36:52,500
Oh, it's a rat.

358
00:36:53,500 --> 00:36:56,500
Mr. Tian, I'm afraid of the rat.

359
00:36:57,500 --> 00:36:58,500
Sir.

360
00:37:09,500 --> 00:37:10,500
Aunt Jia.

361
00:37:11,500 --> 00:37:12,500
What are you doing here?

362
00:37:14,500 --> 00:37:18,500
I've come to clean up. Just finished now. Excuse me.

363
00:37:19,500 --> 00:37:23,500
Cleaning, but I didn't see you carrying a broom or a piece of cloth.

364
00:37:26,500 --> 00:37:29,500
And what is this? An incense cone?

365
00:37:30,500 --> 00:37:33,500
Are you thinking of using the scent to seduce Mr. Tian?

366
00:37:35,500 --> 00:37:37,500
He doesn't like anything with strong scent

367
00:37:38,500 --> 00:37:39,500
or spicy like this.

368
00:37:41,500 --> 00:37:42,500
I know

369
00:37:43,500 --> 00:37:45,500
that you want Mr. Tian to be your husband so bad.

370
00:37:46,500 --> 00:37:48,500
But he's getting married.

371
00:37:49,500 --> 00:37:50,500
Don't mess with him again.

372
00:37:51,500 --> 00:37:53,500
If you mess this up,

373
00:37:54,500 --> 00:37:57,500
I will tell Madam to punish you hard.

374
00:37:57,800 --> 00:37:58,500
Remember this.

375
00:38:06,500 --> 00:38:08,500
Delivery schedule

376
00:38:37,500 --> 00:38:39,500
Thanks a lot.

377
00:38:53,500 --> 00:38:54,500
Done.

378
00:38:56,500 --> 00:38:58,500
Then I'll keep it in its place.

379
00:38:58,800 --> 00:38:59,500
Yeah.

380
00:39:08,500 --> 00:39:10,500
You help me like this during this time.

381
00:39:11,500 --> 00:39:14,500
When you read and write more fluently, you will work faster.

382
00:39:18,500 --> 00:39:19,500
Last night,

383
00:39:20,500 --> 00:39:23,500
I drew pictures and write the words for you.

384
00:39:24,500 --> 00:39:29,500
You'll be able to understand more easily and memorize letters faster too.

385
00:39:31,500 --> 00:39:32,500
Here.

386
00:39:42,500 --> 00:39:43,500
Did you draw these all by yourself?

387
00:39:44,500 --> 00:39:45,500
Yeah.

388
00:39:54,500 --> 00:39:56,500
I think we'd better start studying now?

389
00:39:57,500 --> 00:39:58,500
Yeah.

390
00:40:09,500 --> 00:40:10,500
Sorry.

391
00:40:18,500 --> 00:40:19,500
Did you hurt?

392
00:40:20,500 --> 00:40:21,500
No.

393
00:40:22,500 --> 00:40:23,500
Where did you get hit?

394
00:40:26,500 --> 00:40:27,500
Here.

395
00:40:28,000 --> 00:40:28,500
Did it swell?

396
00:40:31,500 --> 00:40:32,500
Tian.

397
00:40:35,500 --> 00:40:37,500
Yang, what's the matter?

398
00:40:44,500 --> 00:40:45,500
Pin is here.

399
00:40:48,500 --> 00:40:51,500
You stay here looking at the pictures for a while. I'll be right back.

400
00:40:57,500 --> 00:40:58,500
Let's go, Yang. Go.

401
00:41:17,500 --> 00:41:19,500
The publisher just sent the flyers to me.

402
00:41:19,900 --> 00:41:21,500
I will put them in different places.

403
00:41:22,500 --> 00:41:24,500
So I want to take you with me.

404
00:41:25,500 --> 00:41:30,500
But since I'm here, it will be strange if I don't meet you.

405
00:41:31,000 --> 00:41:32,500
Did I bother you?

406
00:41:36,500 --> 00:41:37,500
Not at all.

407
00:41:38,500 --> 00:41:39,500
What bother?

408
00:41:40,500 --> 00:41:44,500
You are considered Tian's younger sister.

409
00:41:45,500 --> 00:41:48,500
If this land is sold in the future, and you are you free,

410
00:41:50,500 --> 00:41:51,500
you will become his sister-in-law as well.

411
00:41:52,500 --> 00:41:55,500
Yang, what are you talking about?

412
00:41:56,500 --> 00:41:57,500
I think I'm blushing now.

413
00:42:00,500 --> 00:42:01,500
Let me put it back.

414
00:42:01,800 --> 00:42:02,500
Thanks.

415
00:42:49,500 --> 00:42:52,500
I think we'd better review what we've learned.

416
00:42:53,000 --> 00:42:55,500
So I can teach you something new.

417
00:42:59,500 --> 00:43:00,500
Jiu.

418
00:43:01,500 --> 00:43:02,500
Do you hear me?

419
00:43:03,500 --> 00:43:04,500
Yes.

420
00:43:09,500 --> 00:43:11,500
Is the woman who came to see you today your fiancée?

421
00:43:13,500 --> 00:43:14,500
Lady Pin?

422
00:43:14,700 --> 00:43:15,500
Right.

423
00:43:18,500 --> 00:43:19,500
She's pretty.

424
00:43:21,500 --> 00:43:26,500
Besides her pretty face, she is also a smart woman.

425
00:43:28,500 --> 00:43:30,500
A woman who dares to think and do.

426
00:43:31,500 --> 00:43:34,500
I'm very lucky to have her as my fiancée.

427
00:43:36,500 --> 00:43:37,500
If it was someone else,

428
00:43:38,500 --> 00:43:40,500
I probably wouldn't be at ease like this.

429
00:43:47,500 --> 00:43:48,500
I think we should not study today.

430
00:43:50,500 --> 00:43:51,500
I have a headache.

431
00:44:08,500 --> 00:44:10,500
Should we go pick up Nangnoi?

432
00:44:11,500 --> 00:44:13,500
More people will finish sticking the flyers fast.

433
00:44:14,500 --> 00:44:15,500
I think that's good too.

434
00:44:17,500 --> 00:44:18,500
Madam.

435
00:44:18,800 --> 00:44:19,500
Aunt Li.

436
00:44:25,500 --> 00:44:27,500
Where is Tian? Why are you two here alone?

437
00:44:30,500 --> 00:44:33,500
Tian is at work. So I have to give Pin a ride instead.

438
00:44:37,500 --> 00:44:40,500
If Pin is going home, I'll let the chauffeur give you a ride.

439
00:44:41,500 --> 00:44:44,500
You are alone with the fiancé's younger brother like this.

440
00:44:45,500 --> 00:44:49,500
I think it isn't proper in eyes of other people.

441
00:44:52,500 --> 00:44:56,500
I know that you are an honorable girl

442
00:44:57,500 --> 00:44:58,500
from a noble family.

443
00:44:59,500 --> 00:45:01,500
You won't do anything to damage your reputation.

444
00:45:02,500 --> 00:45:04,500
But we can't stop others' words.

445
00:45:06,500 --> 00:45:07,500
Be careful.

446
00:45:51,500 --> 00:45:52,500
Madam.

447
00:45:53,500 --> 00:45:56,500
If you don't have anything to say to me, please excuse me.

448
00:45:57,100 --> 00:45:59,500
A toad wishing to eat swan meat.

449
00:46:00,500 --> 00:46:01,500
Don't know your place.

450
00:46:04,500 --> 00:46:06,500
What do you mean?

451
00:46:07,500 --> 00:46:08,500
Don't act like you don't know.

452
00:46:09,500 --> 00:46:11,500
I saw your eyes when you looked at Pin.

453
00:46:12,500 --> 00:46:15,500
You have feelings for your brother's lover.

454
00:46:17,500 --> 00:46:18,500
You're just a son of the second wife.

455
00:46:19,500 --> 00:46:21,500
Are you planning to steal the stuff of Song Family's heir?

456
00:46:23,500 --> 00:46:24,500
Your mom must have taught you well.

457
00:46:29,500 --> 00:46:31,500
I think you think too much.

458
00:46:32,500 --> 00:46:36,500
Not everyone thinks about power and destiny all the time.

459
00:46:37,500 --> 00:46:40,500
If it's Tian's loved ones, I won't bother for sure.

460
00:46:41,500 --> 00:46:44,500
But are you sure that Tian loves this?

461
00:46:44,900 --> 00:46:45,500
Yang.

462
00:46:51,500 --> 00:46:52,500
How dare you?

463
00:46:53,500 --> 00:46:56,500
I was too kind to you in the past.

464
00:47:05,500 --> 00:47:06,500
Yang is really bad.

465
00:47:07,500 --> 00:47:09,500
Perhaps, he finds a way to get closer to Lady pin

466
00:47:09,900 --> 00:47:11,500
because of an order of Madam Chan.

467
00:47:12,500 --> 00:47:16,500
These two are always trying to destroy you and Mr. Tian.

468
00:47:17,500 --> 00:47:19,500
Keep an eye on Yang.

469
00:47:20,300 --> 00:47:21,500
Don't let him come near Pin again.

470
00:47:22,500 --> 00:47:23,500
Yes, madam.

471
00:47:25,500 --> 00:47:29,500
We have to be careful not only Mr. Yang, but also Mud.

472
00:47:29,800 --> 00:47:32,500
Today, I met her in Mr. Tian's room again.

473
00:47:33,000 --> 00:47:34,500
She's really thinking of seducing Mr. Tian.

474
00:47:37,500 --> 00:47:38,500
In fact,

475
00:47:39,500 --> 00:47:42,500
If Mud sleeps with Tian,

476
00:47:43,500 --> 00:47:44,500
I think it will be good.

477
00:47:45,500 --> 00:47:48,500
Maybe if he sleeps with a girl,

478
00:47:50,500 --> 00:47:51,500
he might like it.

479
00:47:53,500 --> 00:47:55,500
And if they can have children together, it's even better.

480
00:47:59,500 --> 00:48:01,500
Do you really think so?

481
00:48:43,500 --> 00:48:44,500
What are you doing?

482
00:48:49,500 --> 00:48:50,500
I secretly keep it.

483
00:48:51,500 --> 00:48:55,500
The orchid dust is the one that causes mushrooms to grow out of insects.

484
00:48:56,500 --> 00:48:58,500
Are you going to produce the beetle orchid again?

485
00:48:59,500 --> 00:49:01,500
Who are you going to kill ? We're now being watched.

486
00:49:02,500 --> 00:49:04,500
If we do something that is risky, or if someone dies,

487
00:49:05,100 --> 00:49:06,500
people are more suspicious of us.

488
00:49:07,100 --> 00:49:08,500
I'm not going to make beetle orchids.

489
00:49:10,500 --> 00:49:13,500
Orchid dust can produce many types of orchids.

490
00:49:14,500 --> 00:49:18,500
If we put it in the beetles, it will become beetle orchids.

491
00:49:19,500 --> 00:49:22,500
But if we put the orchid dust in the cicada,

492
00:49:23,500 --> 00:49:25,500
it will become cicada orchids.

493
00:49:26,500 --> 00:49:27,500
What is the poison of cicada orchid?

494
00:49:28,500 --> 00:49:30,500
It's not poisonous.

495
00:49:31,100 --> 00:49:33,500
But it has arousal property.

496
00:49:38,500 --> 00:49:41,500
Good. Hurry up finishing this orchid.

497
00:49:42,500 --> 00:49:44,500
If we want Tian to have a wife and children,

498
00:49:45,500 --> 00:49:46,500
we need this.

499
00:49:47,500 --> 00:49:48,500
It's the orchid dust.

500
00:49:59,500 --> 00:50:01,500
Here.

501
00:50:03,500 --> 00:50:06,500
Tian, thank you so much for coming.

502
00:50:07,500 --> 00:50:09,500
Since Madam saw me and Pin,

503
00:50:10,000 --> 00:50:11,500
she always keeps an eye on me until I can't go anywhere.

504
00:50:13,500 --> 00:50:16,500
For my brother's happiness, I can do more than this.

505
00:50:18,500 --> 00:50:20,500
Yang, Tian.

506
00:50:24,500 --> 00:50:27,500
Does Aunt Li follow us again?

507
00:50:28,500 --> 00:50:31,500
Don't worry. Tian is coming with us. It's okay.

508
00:50:34,500 --> 00:50:35,500
Let's go.

509
00:50:37,500 --> 00:50:38,500
Okay.

510
00:50:41,500 --> 00:50:42,500
Excuse me.

511
00:50:43,500 --> 00:50:44,500
Let's go.

512
00:50:52,500 --> 00:50:55,500
That day when Aunt Li talked to you, what did she say?

513
00:50:56,500 --> 00:50:58,500
If you're with me, you must be laughing.

514
00:50:59,000 --> 00:51:02,500
Because she said that I was a toad wishing to eat swan meat.

515
00:51:04,500 --> 00:51:05,500
She was right.

516
00:51:06,100 --> 00:51:09,500
Whoa, you are a swan? I think you are a moth.

517
00:51:10,500 --> 00:51:11,500
You see me as a moth?

518
00:51:12,500 --> 00:51:14,500
That's right, so others don't eat this moth.

519
00:51:14,800 --> 00:51:16,500
Only this toad can eat you.

520
00:51:21,500 --> 00:51:22,500
About my land,

521
00:51:23,000 --> 00:51:25,500
someone just contacted me. He's interested.

522
00:51:25,900 --> 00:51:26,500
He made an appointment to see the land in two days.

523
00:51:27,500 --> 00:51:28,500
Really?

524
00:51:28,900 --> 00:51:29,500
I'll accompany you then.

525
00:51:30,500 --> 00:51:33,500
Because if you sell it, you will have money to buy back the palace from Madam Li.

526
00:51:34,500 --> 00:51:35,500
So that you don't have to marry Tian.

527
00:51:36,500 --> 00:51:37,500
Right, Tian?

528
00:51:40,500 --> 00:51:41,500
Where did he go?

529
00:51:51,500 --> 00:51:52,500
He's here.

530
00:51:55,500 --> 00:51:57,500
Tian, you are here.

531
00:51:58,500 --> 00:51:59,500
You go in first.

532
00:52:01,500 --> 00:52:02,500
What's up?

533
00:52:03,500 --> 00:52:07,500
Something bothering your mind? You can tell me.

534
00:52:08,500 --> 00:52:10,500
You've helped me a lot. Let me help you as well.

535
00:52:11,500 --> 00:52:14,500
It's nothing. I must be thinking too much.

536
00:52:15,500 --> 00:52:17,500
Come on, tell me what's on your mind. Go on.

537
00:52:20,500 --> 00:52:25,500
I don't know if Jiu is angry or upset with me.

538
00:52:26,500 --> 00:52:30,500
Jiu? The one you teach him?

539
00:52:31,000 --> 00:52:31,500
Yeah.

540
00:52:33,500 --> 00:52:35,500
Recently, he doesn't seem to talk much.

541
00:52:36,500 --> 00:52:38,500
He didn't come to study.

542
